    "# Credit Card Fraud Detection — Model Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "In the previous project, feature engineering did not improve fraud detection performance.  \n",
    "This suggests that the next logical step is to focus on **model optimization**.\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we optimize the Random Forest model by:\n",
    "\n",
    "- tuning important hyperparameters\n",
    "- comparing baseline vs tuned performance\n",
    "- adjusting the classification threshold\n",
    "- evaluating which setup gives the best fraud detection trade-off\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "The main goals of this notebook are to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. prepare the fraud dataset for modeling\n",
    "2. train a baseline Random Forest model\n",
    "3. optimize the model using improved hyperparameters\n",
    "4. compare both models using fraud-aware metrics\n",
    "5. tune the classification threshold\n",
    "6. identify the most practical fraud detection setup\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why Model Optimization Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "A model’s performance is not determined only by the data — it also depends on:\n",
    "\n",
    "- model architecture\n",
    "- hyperparameter choices\n",
    "- decision threshold\n",
    "\n",
    "Sometimes, the same model can produce better fraud detection results simply by being tuned more carefully.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is especially important in fraud detection, where the goal is not just accuracy, but balancing:\n",
    "\n",
    "- fraud detection rate (**recall**)\n",
    "- reliability of fraud alerts (**precision**)"
   ]
