    "### Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset is highly imbalanced, with:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **1,842,743 legitimate transactions (class 0)**\n",
    "- **9,651 fraudulent transactions (class 1)**\n",
    "\n",
    "This corresponds to a fraud rate of approximately **0.52%**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why this matters\n",
    "\n",
    "This extreme imbalance means that:\n",
    "\n",
    "- A model can achieve very high **accuracy** by simply predicting all transactions as non-fraud  \n",
    "- Accuracy alone is therefore **misleading** for this problem  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Because fraud cases are rare:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The model must be evaluated using:\n",
    "  - **Precision** → how reliable fraud predictions are  \n",
    "  - **Recall** → how many fraud cases are detected  \n",
    "  - **F1-score** → balance between precision and recall  \n",
    "  - **ROC-AUC** → overall discrimination ability  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Practical Implication\n",
    "\n",
    "In real-world fraud detection:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Missing fraud (**false negatives**) can result in financial loss  \n",
    "- Flagging legitimate transactions (**false positives**) can affect customer experience  \n",
    "\n",
    "This creates a critical trade-off between precision and recall\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Conclusion from this section\n",
    "\n",
    "The strong class imbalance reinforces that:\n",
    "\n",
    "> Model optimization must focus on improving fraud detection (recall)  \n",
    "> without significantly increasing false alarms.\n",
    "\n",
    "This will guide the tuning strategies used later in this notebook."
   ]
